{"questionId":"15811","questionHtml":"<p>Deduce that the eigenvalues are real if <em><strong>A</strong></em> is symmetric.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>if the matrix is symmetric, <em>b</em> = <em>c</em>. In this case,&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\left( {a - d} \\right)^2} + 4bc = {\\left( {a - d} \\right)^2} + 4{b^2} \\geqslant 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>d</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>b</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>⩾</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>because each square term is non-negative&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"15811","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ0.F_3a.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Deduce that the eigenvalues are real if A is symmetric.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}